This Righteouſneſs of the Law, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 is nothing elſe but the juſt Puniſhment due to ſin, by Vertue of Gods Law, and the Threatnings thereof, all one with that 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
Rom: 1. and laſt. For that is meant of the Righteouſneſs of God, that is, the Puniſhment due to ſin by vertue of Gods juſtice, for it is all one Puniſhment that is due by vertue of divine juſtice or by Vertue of the Threatning Law. Now this Puniſhment due by Law is ſaid to be fulfilled in us, by Gods Puniſhing ſin in Chriſt; For though God did diſpenſe ſo far with the ſevere Threatning of the Law, as that he would not inflict that ſevere Puniſhment on the Tranſgreſſor himſelf, yet theſe ſevere Puniſhments for kind, that were Threatned by the Law againſt Tranſgreſſors, God, in Puniſhing Chriſt, he inflicted theſe upon him, and therefore, Heb. 2.14. It is ſaid, that he behooved to become man that he might bear Death, the particular Puniſhment threatned againſt the ſin of man by the Law, And therefore the Scripture aſſerts, that Chriſt bore no other Curſe but the Curſe of the Law;
for the Law threatning, was the Rule by which Juſtice did proceed in inflicting puniſhment on the Mediator, And therefore it is ſaid, Gal. 4 4 He was made under the Law.

